File: Controversial Nigerian pastor Timothy Omotoso. JOHANNESBURG - Lawyers for rape accused Timothy Omotoso have concluded their arguments for leave to appeal a judge's decision to deny him bail. The Nigerian televangelist was arrested by the Hawks in 2017. READ: Omotoso back in court, continues fight He faces many charges, including those of rape and human trafficking. This is the third time Omotoso tries to get himself off the hook and applying to reverse the decision.